Heat oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Add onion, carrot, and celery; cook 6 minutes or until onion is translucent, stirring frequently. Add dill and garlic, and cook 1 minute or until tender, stirring constantly. Add broth, lentils, and tomatoes. Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat, and simmer 15 minutes or until lentils are tender. Add chickpeas to pan. Cook 1 minute or until thoroughly heated. Stir in lemon juice just before serving.